# Example TLS SNI passthrough routing for Boxion edge proxy
#
# Map $ssl_preread_server_name (SNI) to an upstream. The upstream can be
# - a service name:port on the Docker network (e.g., api:8443 if you terminate TLS there), or
# - an IPv6 address in brackets with port for true passthrough to a Boxion client IP.
# The default (in nginx.conf) is caddy:8443 if no match is found.
#
# Syntax: <hostname> <upstream>;
#
# Route dashboard/API to API container with TLS offload elsewhere (usually not needed):
# tunnel.milkywayhub.org    api:8443;
#
# Example: passthrough to a Boxion-assigned IPv6 endpoint on 443
# site1.example.org         [2001:db8:1234:5678::120]:443;
